== shooting down of Mustang ==

I have removed the following:
"An American p51 mustang plane was said to have been shot down nearby by accident, but is believed by many to be a rumour." After 12 months, there was no supporting reference. [[User:Rjm at sleepers|Rjm at sleepers]] ([[User talk:Rjm at sleepers|talk]]) 08:06, 21 March 2008 (UTC)

== Content of Most Haunted episodes ==

The article contains a description of the contents of the Coalhouse Fort episodes of the TV programme ''Most Haunted''. This description is sourced to a Youtube video of the programme. The programme itself cannot be a secondary source for the content of the programme and in view of the Ofcom ruling, is not in any case a reliable source for information about hauntings. Although the content contains words such as "claimed" and "allegedly", I believe it is unencyclopedic and should be removed. [[User:Rjm at sleepers|Rjm at sleepers]] ([[User talk:Rjm at sleepers|talk]]) 07:21, 6 July 2011 (UTC)
:No one seems to object, so I will move all the stuff about ''Most Haunted'' to the article about the TV programme. [[User:Rjm at sleepers|Rjm at sleepers]] ([[User talk:Rjm at sleepers|talk]]) 08:21, 20 July 2011 (UTC)

==Not Napoleonic==

While there was a 1795 battery here, it was obliterated when this fort was built, so I don't think it should be in the Napoleonic Forts category [[User:Vicarage|Vicarage]] ([[User talk:Vicarage|talk]]) 11:00, 27 January 2012 (UTC)

